  "response": "Some animals that are generally not recommended or suitable for domestication include:\n\n1. Wild predators\n- Tigers\n- Lions\n- Wolves\n- Leopards\n- Bears\n\n2. Venomous animals\n- Snakes\n- Scorpions\n- Some spiders\n\n3. Large, dangerous animals\n- Hippos\n- Crocodiles\n- Great apes\n- African elephants\n\n4. Highly aggressive animals\n- Hyenas\n- Cheetahs\n- Wild boars\n\n5. Animals with complex social structures\n- Dolphins\n- Whales\n- Most primates\n\n6. Specialized wild animals\n- Most exotic species\n- Animals with specific habitat requirements\n\nReasons for not taming these animals include:\n- Safety risks\n- Ethical concerns\n- Inability to meet their complex needs\n- Potential harm to the animal\n- Legal restrictions\n- Difficulty in providing appropriate care\n\nWhile some individuals might attempt to domesticate these animals, it's generally not recommended by wildlife experts and conservationists.",
